node.title: Live: Two new ‘high-risk’ locations of interest as Omicron outbreak grows to 105 cases
node.content: ["The Ministry of Health announced on Friday that there were 105 new COVID-19 community cases (of any variant) and a further 15 Omicron cases taking the total confirmed or suspected cases of the new variant to 105.\u00a0", "The ministry on Friday announced a further 68 locations of interest around the country including 17 'close contact' locations linked to an Omicron case where people need to self-isolate and get a test immediately. Two new 'high risk' locations of interest were added on Saturday morning.", "\u00a0", "\u00a0", "Follow Newshub's live updates below - app users, click here", "\u00a0"]
